THAT DO, THOUGH.

14:16.029 --> 14:17.552
WHAT'S HAPPENING?

14:17.595 --> 14:19.946
ALL WILL BE REVEALED. THEIR RING
IS IN YOUR RIGHT HAND.

14:19.989 --> 14:21.164
UH, SIR,
YOU'VE MADE A MISTAKE.

14:21.208 --> 14:22.078
WE'VE GOT THE RING
RIGHT HERE.

14:22.122 --> 14:23.558
UH, THAT'S A REPLICA.

14:23.601 --> 14:24.951
A...REPLICA?

14:24.994 --> 14:27.214
HE DID A FRENCH DROP
TO SWAP THE VALUABLE RING

14:27.257 --> 14:28.737
WITH A CHEAP REPLICA.

14:28.780 --> 14:30.434
FRENCH DROP IS A SLEIGHT-OF-HAND
MOVE. NOT IMPORTANT.

14:30.478 --> 14:33.089
THAT RING NEVER BELONGED
TO YOUR GRANDMOTHER,

14:33.133 --> 14:35.048
AND IT'S NOT
A REAL DIAMOND.

14:35.091 --> 14:36.919
IS THAT TRUE?OF COURSE NOT.

14:36.963 --> 14:39.617
HE WOULD STUDY THE RING
THAT HE JUST GAVE YOU,

14:39.661 --> 14:42.620
THEN BREAK THE SAD NEWS THAT
YOUR GRANDMA'S RING IS A PHONY,

14:42.664 --> 14:44.013
AND YOU'D BE
NONE THE WISER.

14:44.057 --> 14:45.667
[ LAUGHS ]
THIS IS INSANE.

14:45.710 --> 14:47.974
THEN YOU WON'T MIND OPENING UP
YOUR RIGHT HAND, WILL YOU?

14:50.802 --> 14:54.850
OPEN UP YOUR RIGHT HAND,
PLEASE, SIR.

14:54.894 --> 14:56.286
HOLY MOLY.

14:56.330 --> 14:57.461
WELL, THANK YOU FOR
YOUR ASSISTANCE, FOLKS.

14:57.505 --> 14:58.941
I'LL TAKE IT
FROM HERE.

14:58.985 --> 15:00.508
UH...

15:00.551 --> 15:02.162
DON'T WORRY, MA'AM.
THE REAL RING IS IN YOUR HAND.

15:02.205 --> 15:03.250
GOOD DAY TO YOU.

15:03.293 --> 15:05.948
THANK YOU.MY PLEASURE.

15:07.558 --> 15:10.779
SO, MY CROOKED FRIEND,
TODAY IS YOUR LUCKY DAY.

15:10.822 --> 15:12.302
IS IT?[ DOOR CLOSES ]

15:12.346 --> 15:13.956
WELL, ON A NORMAL DAY,
YOU'D BE OFF TO THE POKEY NOW.

15:14.000 --> 15:18.656
BUT AS IT HAPPENS...I'M IN
THE MARKET FOR A DIAMOND RING.

15:18.700 --> 15:20.528
OH.
OH.

15:20.571 --> 15:22.530
SO SHOW ME YOUR
VERY BEST SELECTION, PLEASE.

15:22.573 --> 15:28.318
AND, SIR, IF I SEE ANY GLASS...
THE CUFFS WILL COME OUT.

15:30.016 --> 15:31.539
NOTHING TOO GAUCHE.

15:37.501 --> 15:38.546
[ KNOCK ON DOOR ]

15:38.589 --> 15:40.243
WHAT'S UP?

15:40.287 --> 15:41.941
TORK JUST CALLED IN
FROM THE CRIME SCENE.

15:41.984 --> 15:43.594
NO INTACT CORPSES
IN THE BASEMENT,

15:43.638 --> 15:45.945
BUT A LOT OF BODY PARTS,
BADLY BURNED AND FRAGMENTED.

15:45.988 --> 15:47.598
HAVE THEM RUSH
THE DNA TESTS.

15:47.642 --> 15:49.470
PULL SOME STRINGS
IF YOU HAVE TO.

15:49.513 --> 15:52.299
WHY THE RUSH?STILL GOT A LOT
OF MEDIA INTEREST.

15:52.342 --> 15:54.083
THE BOSSES WANT TO BE
ABLE TO ANNOUNCE WE GOT THE GUY.

15:54.127 --> 15:57.043
FOR THAT, WE NEED A CORONER'S
REPORT, SO LET'S GET ON IT.

15:57.086 --> 15:58.958
OKAY, RIGHT AWAY.

16:00.742 --> 16:03.005
HEY, DID ABBOTT GIVE YOU
THE NEWS?
HEY.

16:03.049 --> 16:04.876
WE'RE HAVING A REAL WEDDING
AT HIS HOUSE.

16:04.920 --> 16:06.356
HE DID.

16:06.400 --> 16:07.879
YOU'RE GONNA BE THERE,
RIGHT?
OF COURSE.

16:07.923 --> 16:09.185
I COULD USE YOUR HELP
WITH SOMETHING

16:09.229 --> 16:10.404
IF YOU'RE NOT TOO BUSY.

16:10.447 --> 16:11.709
WHAT'S THAT?

16:14.364 --> 16:16.323
[ SIGHS ]

16:16.366 --> 16:18.238
WHAT DO YOU THINK?

16:20.544 --> 16:22.416
MAKES YOU LOOK SHORT.

16:31.860 --> 16:33.905
SNOW CONE.

16:41.087 --> 16:42.740
SLUTTY ELF.

16:42.784 --> 16:45.917
YOU WANT A SIMPLE PIECE
WITH CLEAN LINES,

16:45.961 --> 16:47.223
MAYBE SOMETHING VINTAGE
AND OFF-WHITE.

16:47.267 --> 16:48.529
WHAT HE SAID.

16:50.922 --> 16:52.359
THANK YOU
FOR DOING THIS.

16:52.402 --> 16:54.317
I ASKED YOU ALONG 'CAUSE
I THOUGHT YOU'D BE HONEST.

16:54.361 --> 16:56.102
I HAD NO IDEA
YOU WERE SUCH A FASHION EXPERT.

16:56.145 --> 16:57.842
NOT ME.

16:57.886 --> 16:59.496
MY MOM COULD RUN UP A
DESIGNER GOWN BEFORE BREAKFAST,

16:59.540 --> 17:01.672
CUT HER CLOTH BY EYE.COOL.

17:01.716 --> 17:03.979
MY MOM HAD A SEWING MACHINE,
BUT IT WAS ALWAYS IN HOCK.

17:04.023 --> 17:06.329
SHE'D BE
VERY PROUD OF YOU.

17:06.373 --> 17:08.201
LOOKING LIKE THIS?

17:08.244 --> 17:09.854
VERY PROUD.

17:09.898 --> 17:13.380
THANK YOU, KIMBALL.

17:14.468 --> 17:16.600
[ INSECTS CHIRPING ]

17:16.644 --> 17:18.298
ALL RIGHT,
GOOD NIGHT, WADE,

17:18.341 --> 17:21.779
AND, UH, TELL SHANIQUA
I SAID THANKS FOR THE FAN MAIL.

17:21.823 --> 17:23.781
[ KEYS JINGLE ]

17:23.825 --> 17:25.435
[ SIGHS ]

17:25.479 --> 17:26.784
[ ALARM CHIRPS ]

17:26.828 --> 17:29.352
[ CHUCKLES ]

17:36.794 --> 17:38.579
EXCUSE ME.

17:38.622 --> 17:41.103
I-I DON'T HAVE
ANY CHANGE, MAN.

17:41.147 --> 17:44.237
OH, HEY, HEY, HEY!
OKAY, OKAY, OKAY.

17:44.280 --> 17:46.108
UH [CLEARS THROAT] HELLO.
YOU CAN TAKE IT.

17:46.152 --> 17:48.502
YOU CAN TAKE IT. HERE.GET IN THE CAR.

17:48.545 --> 17:52.245
DO AS I SAY,
AND YOU WON'T GET HURT.

18:02.429 --> 18:04.257
[ ENGINE TURNS OVER ]

18:11.177 --> 18:12.830
[ INSECTS CHIRPING ]

18:18.314 --> 18:20.838
Keller:
STOP THE VEHICLE.

18:20.882 --> 18:24.146
VERY SLOWLY.
NO ONE GETS HURT.

18:24.190 --> 18:27.018
PUT THE CAR IN PARK
AND GET OUT.

18:27.062 --> 18:29.325
[ GEAR CLICKS ]

18:29.369 --> 18:30.500
EASY.

18:30.544 --> 18:32.328
[ SEAT BELT CLICKS ]

18:32.372 --> 18:34.243
EASY.

18:39.988 --> 18:41.555
GIVE ME YOUR PHONE.

18:41.598 --> 18:43.905
ALL RIGHT.

18:43.948 --> 18:45.167
NO PROBLEMS.

18:45.211 --> 18:47.909
WHAT'S THE PASSCODE?

18:47.952 --> 18:49.998
THERE ISN'T ANY.

18:51.652 --> 18:53.262
WALLET.

18:53.306 --> 18:56.787
LOOK, UH, I ONLY GOT
ABOUT 20 BUCKS IN IT.

18:56.831 --> 19:00.051
AND, UH...
[ CLEARS THROAT ]

19:00.095 --> 19:02.053
WOULD YOU LET ME KEEP
MY DRIVER'S LICENSE?

19:02.097 --> 19:03.620
I-I DON'T WANT TO HAVE TO
GO TO THE DMV.

19:03.664 --> 19:05.883
SURE.

19:12.368 --> 19:14.327
HERE YOU GO.

19:14.370 --> 19:16.372
THANKS.

19:16.416 --> 19:18.200
THANK YOU.

19:18.244 --> 19:19.549
[ THUD ][ SCREAM ]

19:19.593 --> 19:21.072
NO! NO! NO!
[ GRUNTING ]

19:21.116 --> 19:23.249
NO! NO! NO!

19:23.292 --> 19:25.729
[ SCREAMS ]

19:30.560 --> 19:32.519
[ GASPING ]

19:44.444 --> 19:46.185
[ Dialing ]

19:50.450 --> 19:53.104
[ TELEPHONE RINGS ]

19:53.148 --> 19:54.236
TORK.

19:54.280 --> 19:55.890
PATRICK JANE, PLEASE.

19:55.933 --> 19:57.413
UM, SORRY.
HE'S NOT IN.

19:57.457 --> 19:59.763
THIS IS DAN GLOVER
FROM "AUSTIN TODAY."

19:59.807 --> 20:02.592
I INTERVIEWED JANE RECENTLY
ABOUT THIS WHOLE LAZARUS CASE.

20:02.636 --> 20:04.159
SURE. I REMEMBER YOU.

20:04.203 --> 20:06.292
I JUST WANT TO DO A QUICK
FOLLOW-UP. IS HE AVAILABLE?

20:06.335 --> 20:08.990
I'M AFRAID, UH, YOU'RE GONNA
HAVE TO WAIT A FEW DAYS ON THAT.

20:09.033 --> 20:10.252
HE'S OUT OF THE OFFICE
FOR A WHILE.

20:10.296 --> 20:11.558
CAN YOU TELL ME
WHERE I CAN FIND HIM?

20:11.601 --> 20:13.081
IT'LL ONLY TAKE
A FEW MOMENTS.

20:13.124 --> 20:14.865
I'D SAY HE'S PRETTY UNFINDABLE
AT THE MOMENT.

20:14.909 --> 20:16.040
He's getting married
in a few days.

20:16.084 --> 20:18.042
MARRIED?
YEAH.

20:18.086 --> 20:20.610
I CAN, UH, TAKE A MESSAGE,
TELL HIM YOU CALLED.

20:20.654 --> 20:23.004
NO, NO NEED.

20:23.047 --> 20:25.615
OKEYDOKE.

20:25.659 --> 20:27.138
[ BEEP ]

20:30.577 --> 20:32.927
HUH.

20:41.327 --> 20:42.545
Woman:
SIGN RIGHT THERE.

20:42.589 --> 20:44.286
OH, IF I JUST REMEMBERED
HOW TEDIOUS

20:44.330 --> 20:45.809
THIS ASPECT
OF THE MARRIAGE IS,

20:45.853 --> 20:47.811
I MIGHT NOT
HAVE ASKED YOU.SHUSH.

20:47.855 --> 20:49.639
NO, SERIOUSLY.
I'M ONLY ON PAGE TWO.

20:49.683 --> 20:52.468
YOU KNOW, I COULD JUST GIVE
YOU THE RING AND WE COULD ELOPE.

20:52.512 --> 20:55.166
DON'T BE MEAN.
NO TAKE-BACKS.

20:55.210 --> 20:57.168
I COULD GIVE YOU THIS,

20:57.212 --> 20:59.649
AND WE COULD BE IN FIJI
BY NIGHTFALL.

20:59.693 --> 21:02.304
THERE ARE PEOPLE COMING.
WE ARE GETTING MARRIED, DAMN IT.

21:02.348 --> 21:03.305
SUIT YOURSELF.

21:03.349 --> 21:05.481
YOU GOT A RING?
YES, I DID.

21:05.525 --> 21:07.831
MM.
YOU GONNA SHOW IT TO ME?

21:07.875 --> 21:09.659
YOU WANT TO SEE IT?
SHOW ME.

21:09.703 --> 21:11.182
UH, UNH-UNH, UNH.

21:11.226 --> 21:13.359
I'LL TAKE THIS,
AND YOU'LL FILL ALL OF THIS OUT.

21:13.402 --> 21:14.751
[ INDISTINCT CONVERSATION ]

21:16.623 --> 21:19.408
[ SNORTS, LAUGHS ]
OH, MY GOD.

21:19.452 --> 21:21.628
IT'S NOT REAL.
YOU SCARED ME. IT'S FUNNY.

21:21.671 --> 21:22.716
OF COURSE IT'S REAL.

21:22.759 --> 21:24.761
IT'S REAL?
REAL.

21:26.850 --> 21:29.984
OH, MY --
ARE YOU OUT OF YOUR MIND?

21:30.027 --> 21:31.290
YOU LIKE IT?

21:31.333 --> 21:33.640
WELL, IT'S GORGEOUS,
BUT IT'S TOO MUCH.

21:33.683 --> 21:35.816
I-I CAN'T ACCEPT IT.

21:35.859 --> 21:37.861
YOU CAN ACCEPT IT,
AND YOU WILL.

21:37.905 --> 21:39.994
IT'S YOURS.
I WANT YOU TO HAVE IT.

21:40.037 --> 21:41.996
WHAT IS THE JUSTICE
OF THE PEACE'S NAME?

21:42.039 --> 21:43.171
EMILY HAMILTON.

21:43.214 --> 21:45.478
"EMILY HAMILTON."OH, MY...

21:45.521 --> 21:47.871
ALL RIGHT,
LET'S FILE THIS SUCKER.

21:47.915 --> 21:49.656
ALL RIGHT.

21:49.699 --> 21:51.092
WE'LL NEED CONFIRMATION THAT
THE CEREMONY'S BEEN PERFORMED

21:51.135 --> 21:55.052
WITHIN 72 HOURS,
OR YOU WILL NEED TO REFILE.

21:55.096 --> 21:56.402
CONGRATULATIONS.

21:56.445 --> 21:57.925
WHO SAID
ROMANCE IS DEAD?

21:57.968 --> 21:59.274
I CAN'T TAKE THIS.

21:59.318 --> 22:01.102
NO,
NOT YET YOU CAN'T.

22:01.145 --> 22:02.625
WELL, AT LEAST
LET ME TRY IT ON.

22:02.669 --> 22:05.193
NOT YET.
WE DON'T EVEN KNOW
IF IT FITS!

22:07.021 --> 22:10.633
[ ELEVATOR BELL DINGS ]

22:10.677 --> 22:12.331
LISBON, HI.

22:12.374 --> 22:13.984
YES! WYLIE,
DID WE INVITE YOU YET?

22:14.028 --> 22:15.638
NO, NOT YET.
WELL, HERE IT IS.

22:15.682 --> 22:17.640
ABBOTT'S HOUSE,
12:00 SATURDAY.

22:17.684 --> 22:19.163
BUT TRY NOT
TO SPREAD IT AROUND.

22:19.207 --> 22:20.469
WE WANT TO
KEEP IT SMALL,

22:20.513 --> 22:21.905
AND I DON'T WANT TO HURT
ANYBODY'S FEELINGS.

22:21.949 --> 22:24.343
I GOT YOU.
IS THERE A GIFT REGISTRY?

22:24.386 --> 22:25.648
UH, NO GIFTS.

22:25.692 --> 22:26.910
IS THERE A TROUSSEAU?

22:26.954 --> 22:28.608
I DON'T KNOW.
WHAT IS THAT EXACTLY?

22:28.651 --> 22:30.305
NEVER MIND.

22:30.349 --> 22:33.047
Y-You're coming back to work,
right? Here?

22:33.090 --> 22:35.397
[ LAUGHS ]
YEAH, I THINK SO.

22:35.441 --> 22:36.877
Why are you whispering?

22:36.920 --> 22:40.881
LISBON, HEY.
SOMEONE'S TRYING TO REACH YOU?

22:40.924 --> 22:42.709
[ Chuckling ]
OH, MY GOD.

22:42.752 --> 22:45.102
HEY, BOSS.
HI.

22:45.146 --> 22:46.756
I'LL TALK TO YOU GUYS
LATER, OKAY?

22:46.800 --> 22:48.715
IT IS SO GOOD
TO SEE YOU GUYS.

22:48.758 --> 22:50.369
RIGHT BACK AT YOU.[ CHUCKLES ]

22:50.412 --> 22:52.849
WELL, THE NEWS IS SPREADING FAST
THROUGH THE CBI GRAPEVINE.

22:52.893 --> 22:54.155
IT'S TRUE, ISN'T IT?

22:54.198 --> 22:55.722
IT'S TRUE.

22:55.765 --> 22:57.463
OH, WELL, WE HAD TO CALL
AND SAY CONGRATULATIONS.

22:57.506 --> 23:01.162
SO, YOU AND JANE, HUH?
WE ALWAYS KNEW.

23:01.205 --> 23:02.468
WE ALWAYS KNEW?
I ALWAYS KNEW.

23:02.511 --> 23:04.078
HOW ARE THE KIDS?

23:04.121 --> 23:06.994
UH, STICKY, MOSTLY.THE KIDS ARE GREAT.

23:07.037 --> 23:08.648
I KNOW IT'S SHORT NOTICE,
BUT YOU GUYS HAVE GOT TO

23:08.691 --> 23:10.780
COME OUT FOR THE WEDDING.
IT'S SATURDAY.

23:10.824 --> 23:12.434
OH, MY GOSH, OF COURSE.
WE'D LOVE TO.

23:12.478 --> 23:14.741
IT WILL TAKE
A LITTLE CHILD-CARE JUGGLING,

23:14.784 --> 23:16.438
BUT WE CAN SWING IT. YOU KNOW, WORST COMES TO WORST,

23:16.482 --> 23:18.353
WE'LL JUST BRING
THE LITTLE MONKEYS WITH US

23:18.397 --> 23:19.876
AND KEEP THEM LOCKED
IN THE RENTAL CAR.[ SCOFFS ] WILL NOT.

23:19.920 --> 23:20.877
I'M KIDDING.Child: MOMMY!

23:20.921 --> 23:22.836
[ LAUGHS ][ GROANS ]

23:22.879 --> 23:24.185
NO, BUT SERIOUSLY, WE WOULDN'T
MISS IT FOR ANYTHING.MOMMY!

23:24.228 --> 23:25.491
I GOT TO GO.
WE'LL SEE YOU SOON.

23:25.534 --> 23:26.970
ALL RIGHT,
I'LL SEND YOU THE DETAILS.

23:27.014 --> 23:28.145
GREAT. TAKE CARE.

23:37.067 --> 23:39.026
[ INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS ]

23:39.069 --> 23:41.115
[ TELEPHONE RINGING ]

23:42.595 --> 23:43.900
OKAY,
YOU GUYS ARE ALL SET.

23:43.944 --> 23:45.554
IT SHOULD BE IN THE MAIL
THREE TO FIVE DAYS.

23:45.598 --> 23:47.077
THANKS.

23:47.121 --> 23:48.252
[ PEN CLICKS ]

23:48.296 --> 23:50.254
[ KEYBOARD CLACKING ]

23:50.298 --> 23:53.562
EXCUSE ME. I NEED TO FILL OUT
A MARRIAGE LICENSE.

23:54.737 --> 23:56.652
UM, USUALLY THERE'S
TWO OF YOU.

23:56.696 --> 23:59.176
SHE'S RUNNING LATE.
I'LL GET STARTED.

23:59.220 --> 24:02.266
OKAY, WELL, UH, PAPERWORK IS
IN THE END TRAY.

24:02.310 --> 24:03.572
JUST FILL THAT OUT.

24:03.616 --> 24:05.095
WE NEED BOTH OF YOU HERE,
PLUS I.D.

24:05.139 --> 24:08.838
I SEE.
WILL DO, THANKS.

24:15.366 --> 24:17.412
[ TELEPHONE RINGING ]

24:21.764 --> 24:24.332
CITY CLERK'S OFFICE.
PLEASE HOLD.

24:25.420 --> 24:28.945
THANKS FOR HOLDING.
YES, HOW MAY I HELP YOU?

24:28.989 --> 24:30.773
NO, MA'AM.
YOU CAN'T FILE ONLINE.

24:30.817 --> 24:33.472
UNTIL 6:00,
BUT WE'RE CLOSED -- OKAY, BYE.

24:33.515 --> 24:34.647
YOU'RE WELCOME.

24:40.696 --> 24:42.829
LOOKS LIKE
SHE STOOD ME UP.

24:42.872 --> 24:45.484
BAD OMEN FOR A WEDDING,
HUH?

24:52.316 --> 24:54.841
ABBOTT.

24:56.451 --> 24:58.409
CAN I RUN SOMETHING
BY YOU?

24:58.453 --> 24:59.976
YEAH, SHOOT.

25:00.020 --> 25:02.588
SPOT DNA TEST CAME BACK
FROM THE KELLER HOUSE.

25:02.631 --> 25:04.590
SO FAR, ALL THE RECOVERED
BODY PARTS

25:04.633 --> 25:06.548
BELONG TO JOE SR. --
NONE FOR JR.

25:06.592 --> 25:08.245
THEY FOUND HIS GUN,
BUT NOT HIM.

25:08.289 --> 25:10.900
[ SIGHS ]
OH, DAMN.

25:10.944 --> 25:13.076
IT COULD BE THAT HE WAS AT
THE EPICENTER OF THE EXPLOSION

25:13.120 --> 25:15.557
AND WAS VAPORIZED, BUT THERE'S
A STRONG POSSIBILITY

25:15.601 --> 25:17.951
THAT KELLER, A.K.A. LAZARUS,
IS STILL ALIVE.

25:17.994 --> 25:19.561
DAMN.

25:19.605 --> 25:22.216
I LET AUSTIN P.D. KNOW,
AND WE'RE PUTTING OUT A BOLO

25:22.259 --> 25:23.870
TO ALL
THE LOCAL HOSPITALS.

25:23.913 --> 25:25.480
WYLIE'S PUTTING TOGETHER
A K.A. LIST,

25:25.524 --> 25:26.960
AND I'M GONNA HAVE AGENTS SET UP
SHOP AT ALL OF THEM.

25:27.003 --> 25:28.962
WELL, DID YOU PUT OUT
A WIRE JUST IN CASE --

25:29.005 --> 25:31.617
HE RUNS FOR THE BORDER,
YEAH.

25:31.660 --> 25:32.922
ALL RIGHT, WELL,
IT SEEMS LIKE

25:32.966 --> 25:34.271
YOU HAVE EVERYTHING
HANDLED.

25:37.405 --> 25:39.538
I DON'T KNOW IF I SHOULD TELL
JANE AND LISBON.

25:39.581 --> 25:42.541
GOOD QUESTION.
YEAH.

25:44.281 --> 25:46.066
I WOULDN'T.

25:46.109 --> 25:48.111
WE DON'T HAVE ENOUGH
TO BE SURE.

25:48.155 --> 25:50.287
AND, YOU KNOW, THEY'RE
IN A GOOD SPACE RIGHT NOW.

25:50.331 --> 25:52.942
